FR-01: User Authentication

Description:
The system shall allow authorized users to log in using valid credentials.

Acceptance Criteria:

User must enter a valid username and password

System grants access only to authorized users

Invalid credentials display an error message

FR-02: Role-Based Access Control

Description:
The system shall restrict access to features based on user roles.

Acceptance Criteria:

Admin can access all system features

Staff can access only assigned modules

Unauthorized access attempts are blocked

FR-03: Donor Registration

Description:
The system shall allow administrators to register new blood donors.

Acceptance Criteria:

Mandatory donor details must be entered

System stores donor data successfully

Duplicate donor entries are prevented

FR-04: Donor Information Management

Description:
The system shall allow updating and viewing donor information.

Acceptance Criteria:

Admin can edit donor details

Updated data is reflected immediately

Deleted records are removed securely

FR-05: Blood Inventory Management

Description:
The system shall maintain real-time blood stock details.

Acceptance Criteria:

Blood units are updated after each donation

Stock is categorized by blood group

Expired blood units are flagged

FR-06: Blood Request Processing

Description:
The system shall allow hospitals or authorized users to request blood.

Acceptance Criteria:

Requests can be submitted with required details

Requests are approved or rejected based on availability

Emergency requests are prioritized

FR-07: Search & Reporting

Description:
The system shall allow users to search blood availability and generate reports.

Acceptance Criteria:

Users can search by blood group

Reports show accurate inventory data

Reports can be viewed anytime

FR-08: Notification & Alerts

Description:
The system shall notify users about important events.

Acceptance Criteria:

Alerts for low blood stock are generated

Donors receive notifications when required

Expiry alerts are displayed on time
